{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place salmon into a ceramic or glass dish (23 cm).","Place all spices into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>.","Add sugar, salt and thyme and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Evenly coat both sides of salmon with spice mixture. Cover with plastic wrap and place into refrigerator overnight (or a minimum of 8 hours) to cure.","Uncover, turn salmon over, re-cover with plastic wrap and return to refrigerator for 6 hours or until salmon is opaque and firm to the touch (but not tough or dry - see Tips). Rinse fillet under cold water and pat dry with paper towel. Cut into very thin slices to serve (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["500 - 800 g fresh salmon fillet, skin removed if preferred (see Tips)","3 star anise","1 tsp black peppercorns","1 tsp fennel seeds","1 tsp coriander seeds","125 g white sugar","125 g salt","2 sprigs fresh thyme, leaves only","cold water, for rinsing"]}],"id":"r256155","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-z8eG83m5CJM\/XZQxEuDYj5I\/AAAAAAAAcrc\/gdAHeIkZ3oIRT907uLlJ1DDY2ISN9_JLwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lDrvwzat07i_14Jn.png","title":"Anise-cured salmon","publishedAt":"2018-03-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"17.3 g","fat":"11.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"13.3 g","calories":"927.2 kJ \/ 220.8 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ceramic or glass baking dish (23 cm), plastic wrap, paper towel, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Curing time will vary, depending on the size and thickness of your fillet","Serve thin slices of cured salmon, with a dollop of crème fraîche, on pikelets, potato röstis or your favourite toasted bread.","The salmon can be left whole or cut into fillets for this dish."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","14h 10m","10 portions"]}